articles.author: Maayan Lubell, Maya Gebeily
articles.description: The Israeli military said Hezbollah had fired dozens of rockets and several drones into northern Israel on Saturday killing one person, with one drone directed at Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's holiday home, according to his spokesman.
articles.title: Hezbollah fires rockets into northern Israel as Israeli strikes pound Gaza

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Israeli planes dropped leaflets over southern Gaza on Saturday showing a picture of the dead Hamas chief Yahya Sinwar with the message that "Hamas will no longer rule Gaza", echoing language used by Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu.
articles.title: Israel drops leaflets over Gaza showing Sinwar's body and message to Hamas

articles.author: Bianca Flowers, Disha Raychaudhuri
articles.description: Francisca Shaw said she knew something was deeply wrong as she was rushed into an emergency cesarean for the delivery of her third child, a daughter, at Seattle's University of Washington Medical Center in 2015.
articles.title: Black women face a maternal health crisis. Advocates want to make that a US election issue.

articles.author: Dave Sherwood
articles.description: Cuba`s electrical grid collapsed again early on Saturday morning, state-run media reported, plunging the entire country into blackout for a second time just hours after authorities announced they had begun reestablishing service.
articles.title: Cuba`s electrical grid collapses for second time, entire country again without power

articles.author: Steve Holland, Andrea Shalal, Trevor Hunnicutt
articles.description: Democrat Kamala Harris and Republican Donald Trump hit the campaign trail on Saturday, pressing their case with voters from Georgia to Pennsylvania who are already starting to cast ballots in the U.S. presidential election.
articles.title: Harris, Trump court early voters; Usher, Lizzo on the campaign trail

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: The Palestinian militant group Hamas will likely replace Yahya Sinwar with a new political leader based outside Gaza while his brother - Mohammad Sinwar - is expected to assume a bigger role directing the war against Israel in the territory, experts say.
articles.title: Hamas likely to name new leader from outside Gaza after Sinwar's death

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: An Italian coastguard vessel collected migrants that were held in reception centres in Albania and transferred them to Italy on Saturday, after a court ruling dealt a blow to Rome's plans to house migrants picked up at sea outside the EU.
articles.title: Migrants held in Albania transferred to Italy after court ruling

articles.author: Shivam Patel
articles.description: A former Indian government official charged in the United States this week for allegedly directing a foiled murder plot had been arrested in New Delhi in December in an attempted murder case, according to court records and a police officer.
articles.title: India ex-official charged in US murder plot had been arrested in Delhi attempted murder case

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: France's foreign minister said Paris was open to the idea of an immediate invitation for Ukraine to join NATO, but that talks would continue on the subject with allies.
articles.title: France open to immediate Ukraine NATO invite, but more talks needed

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: German Chancellor Olaf Scholz said on Saturday that a project to possibly supply Turkey with Eurofighter jets was an effort being driven by Britain and was in the early stages.
articles.title: Germany says Britain taking lead on possible Eurofighters for Turkey
